## 4. What Is Missing

### 🔴 Authentication & SSO (Priority: Critical)

- [ ] **MeriPehchaan SSO Backend Integration**
  - Implement OAuth2 authorization code flow in [auth](file:///d:/SUVIDHA/gateway/src/middleware/rbacEnforcer.ts#45-72) service
  - `POST /auth/admin/sso/callback` must exchange [code](file:///d:/SUVIDHA/admin-ui/src/store/admin.store.ts#24-45) for tokens with MeriPehchaan
  - Validate `id_token`, extract `ssoSubject`, look up or create `AdminUser`
  - Issue admin JWT with `MUNICIPAL_ADMIN` or `SYSTEM_ADMIN` role
  - **What you need:** MeriPehchaan `client_id`, `client_secret`, and sandbox access

- [ ] **DigiLocker Integration**
  - OAuth2 flow for citizen document verification
  - Pull Aadhaar, PAN, driving license, property documents
  - Store document metadata in `RequestDocument` table
  - **What you need:** DigiLocker `client_id`, `client_secret` from NIC

- [ ] **Aadhaar-based eKYC** (optional, high compliance burden)
  - Biometric/OTP-based authentication via UIDAI API
  - Requires AUA/KUA license and ASA agreement

### 🔴 Payment Gateway (Priority: Critical)

- [ ] **Real Payment Gateway Integration**
  - Currently the payment service uses a mock/demo mode
  - Integrate with BillDesk / Razorpay / PayU for production UPI + Card + NetBanking
  - Implement webhook signature verification
  - Implement payment reconciliation cron (worker exists but needs real data)
  - **What you need:** Merchant credentials, VPA, webhook secret, PCI-DSS compliance

- [ ] **BBPS Live Integration**
  - Replace `bbps-mock` service with real NPCI BBPS Agent API calls
  - Implement mTLS certificate exchange
  - Handle real bill fetch, bill payment, and transaction status APIs
  - **What you need:** NPCI BBPS Agent ID, Agent Secret, mTLS certificates

### 🔴 Database Setup (Priority: Critical)

- [ ] **Run Prisma Migrations**
  - Execute `npx prisma migrate deploy` to create all 20+ tables
  - Verify foreign key constraints, indexes, and triggers

- [ ] **Seed Data**
  - Create at least 1 ULB (e.g., Pune Municipal Corporation)
  - Create wards within the ULB
  - Create at least 1 Kiosk record with valid UUID
  - Create complaint categories for each `ServiceType`
  - Create initial config entries (biller IDs, template IDs, etc.)
  - Create at least 1 `AdminUser` for testing

### 🟡 Utility Services (Priority: High)

- [ ] **Bill Fetch → Real BBPS**
  - Electricity, Gas, Water, Municipal services all currently hit `bbps-mock`
  - Need to wire them to real BBPS UAT sandbox first, then production
  - Each service needs its specific `billerId` configured per ULB

- [ ] **Bill Payment Ledger Settlement**
  - `POST /settle-ledger` on each utility service needs to update local records
  - Payment webhook → utility ledger settlement flow needs end-to-end testing

- [ ] **Real-time Bill Status**
  - After payment, the bill snapshot should be marked as paid
  - Reconciliation worker should poll gateway for settlement status

### 🟡 Notification Service (Priority: High)

- [ ] **Real SMS Delivery**
  - Wire MSG91 or Twilio provider in [sms.worker.ts](file:///d:/SUVIDHA/services/notification/src/workers/sms.worker.ts)
  - Configure DLT-registered SMS templates (mandatory in India)
  - Implement delivery status callbacks
  - **What you need:** MSG91 auth key + DLT template IDs, or Twilio credentials

- [ ] **Push Notifications**
  - Add FCM (Firebase Cloud Messaging) support for mobile PWA
  - Store FCM tokens per user session

- [ ] **Email Notifications**
  - Add SMTP/SES support for admin notifications
  - Receipt email to citizens (if email on file)

### 🟡 Complaint & Grievance (Priority: High)

- [ ] **Photo Upload**
  - Complaint form supports `photoUrl` but no actual file upload endpoint
  - Need object storage integration (MeghRaj S3-compatible or MinIO)
  - Implement `POST /complaints/upload` with multipart form data

- [ ] **Mappls Geolocation**
  - Complaint location currently stubbed
  - Need to integrate MapmyIndia/Mappls API for address autocomplete
  - Reverse geocoding for kiosk-detected coordinates
  - **What you need:** Mappls API key with geocoding permissions

- [ ] **Officer Auto-Assignment**
  - Auto-assign complaints to ward-level officers based on complaint location
  - Escalation rules: unresolved after 48hr → escalate to ULB admin

- [ ] **SLA Tracking**
  - Calculate `expectedResolutionAt` based on complaint priority
  - Dashboard counters for SLA breach, pending, resolved

### 🟡 Service Request (Priority: Medium)

- [ ] **End-to-End New Connection Flow**
  - Service request form → document upload → payment → admin review → approval
  - Currently `request` service is minimal, needs full CRUD routes
  - DigiLocker document pull for identity verification

- [ ] **Document Upload & Verification**
  - Camera capture on kiosk → upload to object storage
  - Admin review panel with accept/reject per document

### 🟢 Analytics (Priority: Medium)

- [ ] **Real Analytics Endpoints**
  - Transaction summary by service type, time period, ULB
  - Complaint statistics: registered vs resolved, average resolution time
  - Kiosk usage: sessions per day, peak hours, most used services
  - Revenue reports: total collections, UPI vs Card breakdown

- [ ] **Kiosk Health Monitoring**
  - Heartbeat API: kiosk sends status every 60s
  - Admin dashboard shows offline/degraded kiosks
  - Alert when kiosk goes offline for > 5 minutes

### 🟢 Bhashini Integration (Priority: Medium)

- [ ] **Speech-to-Text for Voice Input**
  - Currently stubbed with mock responses
  - Need real Bhashini ASR pipeline integration
  - Support Hindi, Marathi, Tamil, Bengali voice input
  - **What you need:** Bhashini API key, pipeline URL, user ID

### 🟢 UI Polish (Priority: Low-Medium)

- [ ] Fix Tailwind `@import` order in kiosk-ui CSS
- [ ] Migrate react-router-dom to v7 (or suppress v6 warnings)
- [ ] Add proper loading skeletons to all pages
- [ ] Add empty states for lists (no bills, no complaints, etc.)
- [ ] Add error boundary pages instead of React's default error screen
- [ ] Keyboard accessibility for kiosk touchscreen
- [ ] Print receipt button integration with thermal printer API

