## 8. Database Migration Checklist

- [ ] Ensure PostgreSQL container is healthy: `docker exec suvidha-postgres pg_isready`
- [ ] Run migrations: `npx prisma migrate deploy --schema=database/schema.prisma`
- [ ] Verify all 20+ tables created: `\dt` in psql
- [ ] Run seed script to populate reference data
- [ ] Verify foreign key relationships work
- [ ] Create audit log trigger (see `database/migrations/003_audit_trigger.sql`)

---

## 9. Security Hardening

### Before Production

- [ ] Replace all placeholder secrets in `.env`
- [ ] Enable HTTPS (TLS 1.2+) for all public endpoints
- [ ] Switch `OTP_MOCK=false` and `BBPS_MOCK=false` etc.
- [ ] Enable `helmet` strict CSP headers
- [ ] Implement CSRF protection for admin forms
- [ ] Set up WAF (Web Application Firewall) rules
- [ ] Enable PostgreSQL connection pooling via PgBouncer (config exists)
- [ ] Enable Redis AUTH in production
- [ ] Implement IP allowlisting for admin endpoints
- [ ] Run OWASP ZAP or equivalent security scan
- [ ] DPDP Act compliance: verify no plain mobile numbers stored
- [ ] Implement audit log rotation and archival

---

## 10. Deployment & DevOps

### CI/CD Pipeline (`.gitlab-ci.yml` exists)

- [ ] Set up GitLab Runner or migrate to GitHub Actions
- [ ] Configure Docker registry for built images
- [ ] Set up staging environment
- [ ] Set up production environment (MeghRaj Cloud)
- [ ] Configure environment-specific `.env` files
- [ ] Set up health check monitoring (UptimeRobot / Prometheus)
- [ ] Set up centralized logging (ELK stack / Loki)
- [ ] Set up alerting (PagerDuty / Slack webhooks)
- [ ] Configure database backups (daily pg_dump + WAL archiving)
- [ ] Configure Redis persistence (AOF already enabled)
- [ ] Load test target: 500 concurrent kiosk sessions
- [ ] Set up disaster recovery plan

---

## Summary: Effort Estimation

| Phase | Effort | Dependencies |
|-------|--------|-------------|
| Phase 1: DB & Seeds | 1 day | None |
| Phase 2: Bug Fixes | 1-2 days | Phase 1 |
| Phase 3: Auth Complete | 3-5 days | MeriPehchaan credentials |
| Phase 4: Payment Gateway | 3-5 days | BillDesk/Razorpay credentials |
| Phase 5: BBPS Live | 5-7 days | NPCI BBPS Agent registration |
| Phase 6: DigiLocker | 3-4 days | NIC credentials |
| Phase 7: SMS/Notifications | 2-3 days | MSG91 + DLT templates |
| Phase 8: Complaints Enhancement | 3-4 days | Mappls API key |
| Phase 9: Analytics | 2-3 days | Phase 1 |
| Phase 10: Production Deploy | 3-5 days | All phases + cloud infra |
| **Total** | **~27-43 days** | — |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Phase 1 (Database & Seeds) and Phase 2 (Bug Fixes) must be completed first.** Without actual database tables and seed data, no service can function properly. The CORS, CSS, and Kiosk payload bugs have been patched in code but need end-to-end verification.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Production deployment requires real credentials from 8+ government/private APIs.** The application process for BBPS Agent registration alone can take 2-4 weeks. Start the credential acquisition process in parallel with development.
